    </nav>
    <div>
      <div class="faq-section" id="section-a">
        <h2>About BridgeDegree (Q1–Q5)</h2>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What exactly is BridgeDegree — is it a course platform or a university?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>BridgeDegree is neither. It is Nigeria's first embedded career infrastructure platform. We do not teach courses or run bootcamps. We build the verified professional identity of Nigerian students — from their first day in university to their first day in a global career — through structured work experience, academic publication support, and a globally legible Career Passport.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Who founded BridgeDegree and when was it launched?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>BridgeDegree was founded in Nigeria in 2026 with the founding insight that Nigerian graduates are systematically invisible to global employers — not because of lack of ability, but because the university system produces academic records and nothing else.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Is BridgeDegree affiliated with any Nigerian university?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>No. BridgeDegree operates independently of any university. We do not require institutional approval or affiliation. Individual lecturers and departmental staff at many universities recommend BridgeDegree to their students — but the platform is not a university product.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Is BridgeDegree a registered and legitimate organisation?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. BridgeDegree is a registered platform operating in Nigeria with documented corporate partner agreements, a publicly visible approved journal whitelist, and a pilot cohort of named students with verified outcomes.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What does 'career infrastructure' mean?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>A coaching service gives you advice and skills. BridgeDegree gives you verifiable credentials. After BridgeDegree, you hold a blockchain-authenticated Career Passport containing 2+ years of documented work experience, at least one indexed publication, and a globally legible professional profile.</p></div>
        </details>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-section" id="section-b">
        <h2>About the Programme (Q6–Q12)</h2>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>When should I join BridgeDegree — is 100 Level too early?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>100 Level is the ideal time to join. The earlier you enrol, the more years you have to build a verified work record before graduation. Your first internship placement begins at 200 Level.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Can I join if I am in 400 or 500 Level?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. Final-year students can join and still benefit from the Publication Pipeline, Career Passport build, and employer placement support.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Are the internships real job placements?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. All internships are structured, performance-tracked placements with formal corporate partners who have signed placement commitments. Each placement has an assigned line manager or mentor and ends with a formal performance review authenticated to your Career Passport.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What is the Publication Pipeline?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>The Publication Pipeline supports the submission of your final-year project to an approved, indexed, peer-reviewed journal. Your existing final-year work is aligned to an industry brief, co-authored with a supervisor or expert, and prepared for submission.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What is the Global Mobility Framework?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>The Global Mobility Framework is a premium add-on. It includes scholarship strategy, SOP development, international CV, ATS calibration, LinkedIn optimisation, NYSC integration, and post-graduation migration support.</p></div>
        </details>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-section" id="section-c">
        <h2>Career Passport & Credentials (Q13–Q16)</h2>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What is the Career Passport?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>The Career Passport is BridgeDegree's flagship credential — a single blockchain-authenticated document that aggregates everything you produce during the programme: internship records, performance reviews, publications, mentor validations, and certifications. It is permanently yours, globally legible, and verifiable by any employer anywhere in seconds.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What does 'blockchain-credentialed' mean?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Your credentials are recorded on a tamper-proof, decentralised digital ledger. Any employer can visit BridgeDegree's verification portal, enter your Passport reference, and instantly confirm the authenticity of your credentials. The record cannot be altered or faked.</p></div>
        </details>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-section" id="section-d">
        <h2>Practical Questions (Q17–Q21)</h2>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How much does BridgeDegree cost?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>BridgeDegree is priced to reflect career transformation. Exact pricing is confirmed during the advisor consultation. Monthly, termly, and annual payment plans are available for all tiers.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Can my parents pay on my behalf — and are there instalment plans?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes to both. Many BridgeDegree students are co-funded by their parents. Instalment plans — monthly or termly — are available for all tiers.</p></div>
        </details>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-section" id="section-e">
        <h2>For Parents (Q22–Q25)</h2>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>As a parent, why should I invest in BridgeDegree for my child?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>The Nigerian university system produces graduates with degrees and nothing else. BridgeDegree builds verified work experience, published research, and a global profile during university — not after. The cost is an investment in an outcome: your child graduating with verifiable credentials that give them a real competitive edge.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How do I know BridgeDegree will deliver what it promises?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>We publish our outcomes. Named student case studies, employer-verified placements, publication submission confirmations, and employer endorsements are all available on our website. We encourage parents to review our case studies and speak with our advisory team before enrolling.</p></div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
